</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Cogn" authorityYear="1891" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia hirtella" order="Myrtales" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirtella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Conostegia hirtella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is quite similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia montana" order="Myrtales" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Conostegia montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a very variable species. It is recognized here on the basis of the presence of stipitate stellate hairs which 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia montana" order="Myrtales" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Conostegia montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks. 
<bibRefCitation author="Schnell, CE" journalOrPublisher="Harvard University" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" refId="B77" refString="Schnell, CE, 1996. The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae). Harvard University" title="The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae)" year="1996">Schnell (1996)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Cogn" authorityYear="1891" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia hirtella" order="Myrtales" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirtella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Conostegia hirtella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia caelestis" order="Myrtales" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caelestis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Conostegia caelestis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of those stipitate stellate trichomes. The much sparser pubescence in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Cogn" authorityYear="1891" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia hirtella" order="Myrtales" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirtella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Conostegia hirtella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
compared to the dense indument in all the plant in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia caelestis" order="Myrtales" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caelestis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Conostegia caelestis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
makes it diffcult to confuse them. Unfortunately 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Cogn" authorityYear="1891" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia hirtella" order="Myrtales" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirtella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Conostegia hirtella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not included in the molecular phylogeny to further help elucidate its close relatives.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
